  "title": "LEMON: MPI Leipzig Mind-Brain-Body EEG (Resting State)",
  "description": "The LEMON dataset comprises resting-state EEG recordings from 215 healthy participants (153 young adults aged 20-35 years and 74 older adults aged 59-77 years) from the Leipzig Study for Mind-Body-Emotion Interactions. Participants performed alternating eyes-open and eyes-closed blocks (~60 seconds each) over approximately 16 minutes of continuous recording using a 62-channel BrainVision actiCHamp system sampled at 2500 Hz. This dataset provides a valuable resource for investigating age-related differences in resting-state brain oscillations and functional connectivity.",
  "methods_description": "EEG was recorded using a BrainVision actiCHamp amplifier with 62 electrodes placed according to the standard 10-20 extended montage (ActiCAP). Online reference was FCz with ground at AFz. Sampling rate was 2500 Hz with impedance maintained below 5 kOhm using active electrodes. Resting-state recordings alternated between eyes-open (fixating on an off LED) and eyes-closed blocks of approximately 60 seconds each, with event markers S200 and S210 indicating eyes-open and eyes-closed onsets respectively.",
